# Security suppressions read by `./workflow.cmd secure.audit` (pip-audit).
#
# One entry per line. Blank lines and `#` comments are ignored.
#
# Format: <VULN_ID>[::YYYY-MM-DD]
#
#   <VULN_ID>       A CVE, GHSA, or PYSEC identifier (letters, digits,
#                   dashes, underscores).
#   ::YYYY-MM-DD    Optional expiry. When the date passes, the entry
#                   stops suppressing and the audit flags the
#                   vulnerability again — forcing a re-review on that
#                   date. Omit the expiry for a permanent suppression
#                   (discouraged — it will never be re-surfaced by CI).
#
# `secure.audit` also merges any `--ignore` CLI value and the
# <PROJECT>_SECURITY_OVERRIDE environment variable into the same list,
# so entries here travel with the repo but can be augmented per-run.
# Invalid entries abort the task with a `file:line: <reason>` message.
#
# Examples (uncomment and edit — do not leave sample IDs active):
#
# CVE-2024-1234::2026-12-31
# GHSA-xxxx-yyyy-zzzz
# PYSEC-2025-0001
CVE-2026-41066
CVE-2026-3219::2026-07-28
